Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
ecoCloneInstGroup(25.10)                              ecoCloneInstGroup(25.10)

Name
       ecoCloneInstGroup - Clones the specified instances

Syntax
       ecoCloneInstGroup

       [-help]

       -maxFanout <integer>

       Clones  the  specified instances. The list of instances to be cloned is
       specified by the setOptMode -opt_clone_insts_list { {...} ... } parame-
       ter.

       The list of instances must be a connex network, with no  connection  to
       the outside from an intermediate instance. Only the instance at the top
       of  the  network can be multi-fanout. All the network is replicated, so
       the same number of clones is made for all the instances within the net-
       work. The instance at the top of the network is determined by the  com-
       mand and it is not user-specified.

       Note:  As an exception to the rule that no intermediate instance should
       connect to a gate outside the specified list of instances,  if  a  gate
       within  the network is a sequential gate, it can have one connection to
       the outside for the scan chain. The clones of the sequential gate  that
       was  part  of a scan chain are inserted in the scan chain. The software
       only considers the flops with the same level of hierarchy and the  same
       scan partition for inserting the clones in the same scan group.

       setOptMode -opt_clone_insts_list { {...} ... }

       ecoCloneInstGroup -maxFanout <max_fanout>

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each ecoCloneInstGroup parameter. For  a  detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command:  man ecoCloneInstGroup

       -maxFanout <integer>
              Specifies the maximum fanout that each cloned instance group can
              drive. This is a required parameter.

Example
       setOptMode  -opt_clone_insts_list   {{subinst/registergate   subinst/i1
       subinst/nandgate}}

       ecoCloneInstGroup -maxFanout 16

